&lt;h1 id=&#34;convex-optimization-凸优化&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#convex-optimization-凸优化&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Convex Optimization 凸优化&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;background-背景阐述&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#background-背景阐述&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; background 背景阐述&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Convex Optimization is just a subfiled of mathematical optimization problem. A convex optimization problem is one in which the objective function and constraint functions are convex, which means they satisfy the inequality:&lt;/p&gt;
\begin{equation}\tag{1.3}\label{eq1.3}
f_i(\alpha x+\beta y) \le \alpha f_i(x)+ \beta f_i(y) 
\end{equation}

